Book Description
================
Tarl Cabot has always believed himself to be a citizen of earth. He 
has no inkling that his destiny is far greater than the small planet 
he has inhabited for the first twenty-odd years of his life. One frosty 
winter night in the New England woods, he finds himself transported 
to the planet of Gor, also known as Counter-Earth, where everything 
is dramatically different from anything he has ever experienced. It 
emerges that Tarl is to be trained as a Tarnsman, one of the most honored 
positions in the rigid, caste-bound Gorean society. He is disciplined 
by the best teachers and warriors that Gor has to offer...but to what 
end? This is the first installment of John Norman's wildly popular and 
controversial Gor series, which has sold millions of copies.
